				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You should be able to address up to 32k of ROM before needing a different mapper besides the simple NROM.
<br />
<br />The NESASM directive to declare two 16k areas of PRG ROM is:
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; .inesprg 2&nbsp; &nbsp;; 2x 16KB PRG code</div><br /><br />Then you can define the banks like so:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; .bank 0<br />&nbsp; .org $8000<br />&nbsp; .bank 1<br />&nbsp; .org $A000<br />&nbsp; .bank 2<br />&nbsp; .org $C000<br />&nbsp; .bank 3<br />&nbsp; .org $E000<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Sounds like you may just be going over the boundary from the $8000 8k bank to the $A000 bank. I think NESASM is just trying to squish it all into the 1 bank where you could actually just relocate some subroutines into the next bank (bank 1) and jump to them there.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

